title: Nature Valley Bike Fest Fun Rides
Afton Road Race and Time Trial
Cal Miller Memorial Bicycle Race
description: The race is on Sunday June 24th starting at 9:00 at Zorbaz restaurant located 1.5 miles north of Perham, MN on County highway 51. The Cal Miller Memorial Race is a 36 mile competitive race. .
course: The race is 3 -  12 mile loops with only right turns. All corners are marshaled and there is a police car with lights for the lead car and for the end.  The course is on open roads but for the final downhill sprint we make every effort to close the road for that short distance. There are age division awards for three places.  The the fee includes a t-shirt and refreshments afterwards.
registration:
The cost of the race is $25.00 for preregistration and $28.00 on race day. All pre-registered riders are guaranteed a T-shirt. Registration begins at 8:00.
This event is in conjunction with Perham\'s annual Turtle fest celebration which starts on June 16th and continues through June 24th.
notes: This race usually averages around 40-55 participants, but has some very fast riders. The average winning time for the 36 miles is usually approx. 1 hours 22-27  minutes.
directions: Perham is located on US Highway 10- approx 180 miles from Minneapolis. Coming on Highway 10 east- take the second exit Highway 78[Battle Lake]. turn right at the ramp and go approx. .7 mile to the second stoplight. turn left and go approx, 1 mile west on Main Street, turning right on County Highway 51, You will cross railroad tracks immediately. Follow the road for 1.5 miles to the north. Zorbaz is a pizza restaurant located on Little PIne Lake. Zorbaz\'s telephone number is 218-346-4900.
